ξ 51. tantumque abest ut . . . ut . . . . The verb abest, abfuit, δια, is always used impersonally by the best writers. The first ut clause is explanatory of the impersonal subject, and the second ut clause depends on tantum, and expresses the result. The predicate of ii is “liberalissimi sint et beneficentissimi‚'’ and the pred. of qui is “ indigeant.’'
